  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Add the<strong> beef mince </strong>and <strong>Marmite</strong> to a bowl with a generous grind of <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Using clean hands, give everything a very good mix up until fully combined</p><p>Divide the <strong>beef mixture</strong> into 8 <span class=\"text-danger\">[16]</span> and roll into meatballs</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1603106667677-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1603106667677-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1603106667677-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1603106667677-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1603106667677-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the<strong> cheddar</strong> into 8 <span class=\"text-danger\">[16]</span> pieces</p><p>Press a piece of<strong> cheddar</strong> into the middle of each meatball<strong> </strong>and seal it in with the beef (make sure there are no gaps) – these are your <strong>cheese-stuffed Marmite meatballs</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1603106828148-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1603106828148-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1603106828148-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1603106828148-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1603106828148-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> meatballs</strong> and cook for 3-4 min, turning occasionally, until browned</p><p>Once browned, transfer the meatballs to a plate and set aside (you'll finish cooking them later!)</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1-1603106845226-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1-1603106845226-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1-1603106845226-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1-1603106845226-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1-1603106845226-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the meatballs are cooking, peel and chop the<strong> red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>finely</p><p>Peel and chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic </strong>finely</p><p>Once the meatballs are done, return the pan to a medium-high heat with any remaining oil</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>red onion </strong>with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until starting to soften</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1603106856682-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1603106856682-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1603106856682-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1603106856682-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1603106856682-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>wholewheat spaghetti</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the spaghetti for 10-12 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the spaghetti, reserving a cup of <strong>starchy pasta water </strong>and drizzle with a little<strong> olive oil</strong></p><p>Tip: The olive oil stops the pasta from sticking together!</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1603106876019-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
